{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"82e1a1ab-9f3c-4aa0-a40e-c268d9b92cf3","content":"It's a small change. In your project file:\n\n**Remove** (or set to `false`):\n```xml\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nThat's the main switch. With **MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0**, `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` is already the **default** runner — `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` was opting you *out* of it. Removing that property opts you back in.\n\n### What changes at runtime\n\n| | VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Run tests | `dotnet test` | `dotnet test` (still works) |\n| CLI args | `--filter`, `--logger` (VSTest syntax) | `--filter`, `--report-trx`, etc. (new syntax) |\n| Direct run | N/A | `dotnet run -- --help` on test project |\n\n### Things to verify after switching\n\n1. **CI scripts** — if you pass VSTest-specific args (e.g. `-- RunConfiguration.TestSessionTimeout=...`), replace them with the new [platform equivalents](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/microsoft-testing-platform-overview).\n2. **`.runsettings`** — still supported, but some options may behave differently.\n3. **TRX output** — use `--report-trx` instead of `--logger trx`.\n4. **Code coverage** — use `--coverage` (Microsoft.CodeCoverage) instead of `--collect \"Code Coverage\"`.\n\nRun `dotnet test` after the change to confirm everything passes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d69cc35e-5153-4728-b7d0-27cb9e966e3c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository doesn't have relevant content. Let me answer from my knowledge about MSTest.Sdk and Microsoft.Testing.Platform migration.","outputTokens":428,"requestId":"E3F8:7A682:1610520:18AE4FD:6A052009"},"id":"20288f15-2150-4c04-bdda-ad682ff139de","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:06:29.259Z","parentId":"b77aaa2a-97c2-4791-8e44-1215341b733d"}
